						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Anonymous wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Hello!<br /><br />I've soldered together the hardware for a copynes...more or less.(I don't have the || port attached yet, but that's not important.)<br /><br />Right now the code burned (flashed) simply disables the add-on circuit and JMPs (FFFC).  <br /><br />The problem: The cart will only start up on a full system power-on, and then only about 1/5 of the time. If I use the reset button on the NES, it NEVER works. (Blank blue screen.)<br /><br />I'm using all 74LS parts for the four small ICs and a MOS 6522 (ripped from an old CMB floppy drive). <br />My ROM is a Winbond (W29EE011-15) Flash ROM. (I have some eproms, but no eprom eraser.)<br />I have bypass caps everywhere, tested the circuit for shorts, double checked every pin and every connection, and everything looks good.<br /><br />I've tested the port bits on the 6522 and the select line on the 157 and everything is as it should be, but no go on the cart. <br /><br />Any help appreciated..</div>
<br />
<br />Hmm, you may have to change one of the caps on the lockout chip circuit... On the PCB it's a .1uF cap but you should replace it with a 1uF.  I forgot to mention this and looks like I should add it to my documentation today before I forget... I don't have an NES right in front of me so I can't quite remember which cap it is; it's next to pin 4 though.  This will lengthen the reset pulse.  I'm not quite sure why this is required but I suspect the 6522 needs a longer reset pulse to operate properly.  BTW, I just remembered and I'm fairly sure that .1uf cap in question is across the reset button so if you got a meter you may be able to find out quicker than it takes me to look and post <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":-)" title="Smile" /></div>

