					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I just checked, and the cap you want to swap out is C8.  It is a .1uf cap and you should remove it and drop a 1uf cap in its place.  Note polarity!  The positive side goes to the large "ground" plane which is really VCC!  The negative side of this cap also connects to pin 7 of the lockout chip, just so you can verify you have the correct capacitor.</div>

